[Name] LyX
[Summary] An advanced LaTeX-based typesetting and text editing program.
[License] GNU General Public License (GPL)
[Description] LyX is an advanced document processor for Unix. It encourages an approach to writing based on the structure of your documents, not their appearance, allowing you to concentrate on writing rather than visual layout. It automates formatting according to predefined rule sets, yielding consistency throughout even the most complex documents.
[Homepage] http://www.lyx.org/
